<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4225] NoSuchColumnFamilyException in multi doesn&apos;t say which family is bad</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4225</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s kind of a dumb one, in HRegion.doMiniBatchPut we do:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
LOG.warn(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;No such column family in batch put&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, nscf);
batchOp.retCodes[lastIndexExclusive] = OperationStatusCode.BAD_FAMILY;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So we lose the family here, all we know is there&apos;s a bad one, that&apos;s what&apos;s in HRS.multi:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
} &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (code == OperationStatusCode.BAD_FAMILY) {
  result = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; NoSuchColumnFamilyException();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can&apos;t just throw the exception like that, we need to say which one is bad even if it requires testing all passed MultiActions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
